Package com.example.mini_pekkas

Class Notifications

java.lang.Object
com.example.mini_pekkas.Notifications
public class Notifications extends Object
The Notifications class represents a notification that includes details such as title, description, date, and priority.

    • Notifications

      public Notifications(String title, String description, Date date, long priority)
      Constructor for creating a Notification object with a Date.
      Parameters:
      title - The title of the notification.
      description - A brief description of the notification.
      date - The date when the notification was created.
      priority - The priority level of the notification (higher value means higher priority).

    • Notifications

      public Notifications(String title, String description, com.google.firebase.Timestamp date, long priority)
      Constructor for creating a Notification object with a Firebase Timestamp.
      Parameters:
      title - The title of the notification.
      description - A brief description of the notification.
      date - The Firebase Timestamp when the notification was created.
      priority - The priority level of the notification (higher value means higher priority).

    • Notifications

      public Notifications(Map<String,Object> map)
      Constructor that creates a Notification object from a Map. The Map is expected to contain keys for "description", "date", "priority", and "title".
      Parameters:
      map - A Map containing key-value pairs representing notification attributes.
